HEADWORD: Saurel
<hw>Sau"rel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any
carangoid fish of the genus <gen>Trachurus</gen>, especially
<spn>Trachurus trachurus</spn>, or <spn>Trachurus saurus</spn>, of
Europe and America, and <spn>Trachurus picturatus</spn> of California.
Called also <altname>skipjack</altname>, and <altname>horse
mackerel</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sauria</ent>⟦br⟧
